# Environment Variables Template

Copy this file to `.env` and fill in your values if you want to use a .env loader (optional).

```bash
EMAIL_HOST=smtp.gmail.com
EMAIL_PORT=587
EMAIL_USE_TLS=true
EMAIL_USERNAME=your@gmail.com
EMAIL_PASSWORD=your-16-char-app-password
EMAIL_FROM=your@gmail.com
EMAIL_TO=rcg19fsu@gmail.com

WEB_HOST=0.0.0.0
WEB_PORT=8000
```

Note: The bot currently reads from environment variables directly. You can source these values:

**PowerShell:**
```powershell
$env:EMAIL_USERNAME = "your@gmail.com"
$env:EMAIL_PASSWORD = "your-app-password"
```

**Linux/macOS:**
```bash
export EMAIL_USERNAME="your@gmail.com"
export EMAIL_PASSWORD="your-app-password"
```
